 Well basing my review souly on my personal opinion out of the box the Case seems well built ; material feels premium until you open the case ;

You know they put serious thought into this !!

It’s freaking massive inside ; more than enough room to build inside the case kinda room !!

Totally impressed ;

Cable management could use some work with in respect they do give you Velcro straps which really don’t hold much but it’s the thought right ; Asus could of came up with something different in that aspect ...

It’s rather straight forward ; the panels are a nice touch ; only issue I have is for someone that’s not used to the fold out doors an pull may yank down an bend the bracket!!

The only thing I didn’t care for what’s so ever is the old cheaply made fan switches ... now that was a no no for me come on ; which I’ll show in my pictures ..

For the price tag that’s where I have a huge issue with ; with no 3.1 hub kinda bugged me since I came from a case that had it ; 3.0 is okay yet they really could included it an USB-C “ASUS” if you are reading this What The Hell guys $246 for a case with no USB-C

The fans I didn’t bother using as I put my LL120s inside so no opinions regarding cooling from them

The airflow in this case is not bad at all ; 1000x better than most I’ve owned ;

Lots of breathing room upfront an on the top panel

An that BEASTY 140mm exhaust fan nice touch;

Partiamo dal presupposto che stiamo parlando di un processore di fascia medio-bassa pensato per configurazioni da ufficio, media center o gaming economiche

Le qualità principali di questo processore a mio parere sono le seguenti:
- Ha un adeguato numero di core/thread (6/12) in grado di supportare carichi di lavoro moderati;
- Ha una GPU integrata (Radeon Vega 7) di tutto rispetto per le aree di utilizzo che ho indicato (in gaming è in grado di offrire un adeguato framerate a 1080p con livello di dettaglio medio) che vi consentirà di realizzare delle build senza una scheda grafica dedicata ma comunque rispettabili;
- Ha un prezzo ottimo in rapporto a ciò che offre;
- Appartenendo ad una famiglia di CPU di precedente generazione può essere montata su architetture AM4 con memorie DDR4 attualmente a prezzi decisamente più bassi delle più nuove AM5/DDR5 o simili della controparte (Intel)

Io personalmente ho acquistato questa APU per realizzare un piccolo media center che tengo in soggiorno del quale sono molto soddisfatto (Asus PRIME A320I-K, 2x16GB Corsair LPX 3600 CL18, Silicon Power A80 512GB NVME, Thermalright AXP120-X67, Case SilverStone SST-SG13B-Q, SilverStone SST-ST30SF 300W)

Per l'utilizzo che ne faccio veramente un ottimo acquisto!!!!

Used this for a cheap upgrade for the family PC which sees light gaming, web browsing and school use (MS office).
Pros:
1) Price/value;
2) low 65w TDP meant I didn't have to upgrade the power supply;
3) Decent desk top performance;
Cons:
1) Only 4 Cores (still adequate for normal desk top use);
2) The 10100f doesn't have built-in graphics.
Note: The requirement for a discrete graphics card isn't really a con, as any cheap/used graphics card will be better than the Intel graphics on the normal i3 10100. Just be aware of this requirement before purchasing.
